</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uisharramoonsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/17/02 8:50:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lost Secrets</span><hr size=1> Isharra searched her robes for her journal, what had become her most trusted friend. Not finding it there, she checked her packs, and then beneath the bed, and then under the rugs of her chamber. No journal. Frantically, she began tearing apart her chambers, Marha at her side, sure she would find her journal among her things. <br>
<br>
They were up until the wee hours of the morn, and finally Marha sent Isharra to bed, where she fell asleep immediately. When she awoke, Isharra continued her search, now retracing her steps the entire evening before. She hadn't written in it in days, though, so it could be anywhere---too many places for her to check. <br>
<br>
Finally, quite vexxed, she ended her search. Hopefully, whoever finds it will not read it, and if they do, they'll not recognize the author. Hopefully, the secrets of her heart were still locked up within her.  <p><i>Isharra Moonsong</i><BR>
<i>Priestess of Tunare</i><br>
<a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/bshadesofgray30856">Shades of Gray</a>

