</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugatsuthewarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GatsuTheWarrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/18/02 8:36:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Flight from Felwithe</span><hr size=1> <br>
The rain of Felwithe fell soft and warm on the streets as the enchanter and his two bodyguards walked out of the office. In the high elves arms was a rather large chest, a symbol on the clasp acting as a a magic lock that would hold any thief at bay.<br>
<br>
The laughing threesome walked joyfully in the late summer rain that felt like a fine mist on their skin. It felt that way to Gatsu as well as he stood in the shadows.<br>
<br>
It had been a long time since he had gotten to wear the gear he had on now, The extra long gnomeskin cloak hung scant inches above the ground and covered everything on him in a lightless black with the exception of his face. That was covered by his hair, now dyed jet-black, which hung damply infront of his eyes. Combined with the training he had received all those years ago there was no way any of the three elves could have seen him.<br>
<br>
They past joyfully right in front of the warrior as he stepped slowly out into the alley behind them. Now they felt his presence but it was already too late.<br>
<br>
The first bodyguard reached for his sword but Gatsus blade was already drawn and ready in his right hand. Gatsus slice was quick and efficient, it came across from Gatsus left to his right side and through the high elfs exposed throat. The gurgling sound that escaped from his neck deafened by a crack of thunder in the distant sky.<br>
<br>
The second bodyguard was a little faster and aimed his backhand-sideways slash at the warriors neck to sever it from his body. Still moving fluidly from the first slash Gatsu spun a full circle as he ducked under the attack. With the sword in his right hand he dug his blade deeply into the side of the elf. As he continued his spin Gatsu brought his left palm against the back of his blade and using his momentum and strength pushed the blade completely through the elfs torso. His legs fell to the floor as his upper body slid into the far alley wall.<br>
<br>
Gatsu raised himself up slowly his steel-cold eyes freezing the enchanter in place before the enchanter could react with a single word to a spell.<br>
<br>
&quot;Nothing personal you know&quot;, Gatsu calmly stated at the target through his own hair hanging lightly in front of his tilted head, &quot;Just business.&quot;<br>
<br>
With those words Gatsu sprang forward lunging with his sword. He drove the elf to the ground, the blade pierced right through the high elfs dainty throat. The politicians eyes, blue with gold flecks, stared pleadingly up at Gatsu. Gatsu smiled evilly at the high elves silent prayer for mercy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bet you wish you had Tunare to pray to eh Gareth.&quot; Gatsu coldly said as he twisted the sword snapping the elves spine and ending his life. Gatsu let the rain wash his blade clean before collecting his prize from the bloodstained alley.<br>
<br>
He leaned over the corpse and took a ring from the finger. Then he took the chest in one hand and left the scene.<br>
<br>
He looked at the chest and recognized the family crest on it, the Moonsong family. As Gatsu passed their estate he tossed the chest through a dark open window. <br>
<br>
As he walked out of Felwithe Gatsu flipped the ring into the air as one would a coin. The emblem of the Crytalbrooke family shone in the dim moonlight. Catching the coin with a sweeping hand he smiles at the trinket. The prize for this ring was indeed high, and he had the inside track on the kill. Gatsu lightly touched the small book safely tucked into his belt.<br>
<br>
With that a shadow passed over the moon and it darkened the night to pitch black. When the light returned the warrior was gone.<br>
